public abstract class PseudoSymbol
extends java.lang.Object
implements Symbol

PseudoSymbol is intended to provide Symbol interface in an object that is not part of the IR.

getIRSymbol

public abstract Symbol getIRSymbol()
Returns the most representative symbol object that exist in the IR. e.g., the symbol of the left-hand-side (base address) for accessy symbol. Depending on the sub-class type of PseudoSymbol this method may return null.
